<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="590" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[811,1457,771,927]" pageId="29" pageNumber="590">DIAGNOSIS. — Reticulated colonies consisting of anastomosing branches. Autozooecia long, having oblong-rectangular shape in deep tangential section, having weakly developed vestibule, arranged in two-three slightly alternating rows on branches. Nodes on low keels present. Cross-section of branches rounded; their dorsal wall thin, carrying thin longitudinal ribs and microacanthostyles.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
